snippet.textDisplay:
I don't think this is in any way related to this episode, but just watching cooking in general got me trying some homemade potato rolls recently that turned out good:
- SUPER rich mashed potatoes for the base. Like, higher end Irish butter rather than the usual stuff. And maybe 50% extra butter? Plus a tub of chive cream cheese.
- THAT went into the potato rolls, which used maybe 25% wheat flour, and some molasses to prime the yeast rather than sugar + honey.
- Per family tradition, upon removing from the oven, coat the hot rolls with butter.
- Used these potato rolls for burgers.
- Of course you gotta grill the buns in butter if you're using them for burgers.

So really, it's just super buttery potato rolls.

Make sure to cook them with something like chicken stock or other flavorants though. 40 minutes at 400F is a good place to start.
